You get to see how
many more stars we

00:37:46.660 --> 00:37:50.410
would see if we could actually
see these M stars in the night

00:37:50.410 --> 00:37:51.370
sky.

00:37:51.370 --> 00:37:54.610
M stars have a couple
of key advantages.

00:37:54.610 --> 00:38:00.230
One is because they're smaller,
a similarly sized planet

00:38:00.230 --> 00:38:04.040
crossing in front is going to
make a bigger transit depth.

00:38:04.040 --> 00:38:07.170
That's very useful for us as
astronomers to detect planets.

