and the simulations I showed,
sort of one of the first times

01:03:37.070 --> 01:03:41.460
that we've been able to do
multiple different magnetic

01:03:41.460 --> 01:03:42.830
field strengths.

01:03:42.830 --> 01:03:44.650
Usually those
numerical simulations

01:03:44.650 --> 01:03:47.650
are so expensive in terms
of the computing time

01:03:47.650 --> 01:03:49.570
you need to run them,
that it's very difficult

01:03:49.570 --> 01:03:50.800
to do a parameter study.

01:03:50.800 --> 01:03:53.560
So we're just now moving into
this area where we can actually

01:03:53.560 --> 01:03:55.190
change all the
relevant parameters

01:03:55.190 --> 01:03:56.860
and see how that affects things.

01:03:56.860 --> 01:04:00.060
Like what kind of stars
will ultimately form out

01:04:00.060 --> 01:04:01.890
of those different simulations.

01:04:01.890 --> 01:04:05.050
And we suspect that in
the high magnetic field

01:04:05.050 --> 01:04:07.620
strength, if you remember
you could see that filament,

01:04:07.620 --> 01:04:09.320
that large filament,
so more mass

01:04:09.320 --> 01:04:11.080
is concentrated
into that filament.

01:04:11.080 --> 01:04:13.470
That'll change how
the gas ultimately

01:04:13.470 --> 01:04:15.110
fragments into stars.

01:04:15.110 --> 01:04:17.840
And so you might get higher
mass stars in that case

01:04:17.840 --> 01:04:21.140
than you would in the cases
where the field was weaker,

01:04:21.140 --> 01:04:24.000
and you have more filamentary
structures, like smaller

01:04:24.000 --> 01:04:26.000
filaments, more
fragmentation, you

01:04:26.000 --> 01:04:28.100
might have smaller
stars forming.

01:04:28.100 --> 01:04:31.560
That will ultimately change
what kind of star you form,

01:04:31.560 --> 01:04:33.350
which then leads
into what Sarah was

01:04:33.350 --> 01:04:37.610
talking about with these
different M dwarfs or G dwarfs

01:04:37.610 --> 01:04:38.880
or K stars.

01:04:38.880 --> 01:04:42.000
That would then change to
have habitability as well.

01:04:42.000 --> 01:04:46.092
So the magnetic field matters.

01:04:46.092 --> 01:04:47.080
-It always does.

