that, actually, we're already

01:13:41.260 --> 01:13:44.390
doing that for planets
that are superearth sized,

01:13:44.390 --> 01:13:46.030
and that are a bit
warmer than Earth.

01:13:46.030 --> 01:13:48.670
So we're already
getting the measurements

01:13:48.670 --> 01:13:50.490
of atmospheres for
planets that are

01:13:50.490 --> 01:13:52.600
very close to what
we eventually want

01:13:52.600 --> 01:13:53.850
to get for Earth like planets.

01:13:53.850 --> 01:13:56.730
So we're nearing that
technological capability.

01:13:56.730 --> 01:13:58.710
And then the next
way to do it, which

